reviews.review_text: Moore is more wow,,,,this is just great ear candy!!

One of My All-Time Favourites A shame Dick cannibalized this show - it's worthy of a release in it's entirety. As amazing as the first set is, the second set just explodes. The first (and best) Sugar Begonias (and the first Sunshine Daydream, unfortunately not included here), and gorgeous renditions of TLMD and Row Jimmy. What I love this show for the most is the stunning WRS, my favourite performance of this tune. The jam that follows travels through different states of matter and has some incredible passages. 
Nice aud recordin, thanks for posting!

Un-Dick's Picks this! There is no reason that the unpublished tracks from this show should not be available to us for streaming. If GDP are going to hack up shows and release only a few songs from a setlist, than the rest of the SBD should be allowed to remain up on the Archive. I love Jerry's AUD, but for some shows you just really need to hear the soundboard to get the full effect. 

Releasing half a show and taking down the whole soundboard is like ripping a few pages out of an encyclopedia and sticking it back on the shelf.

Sugar Mag > Hell in a Bucket > Dark Star in MLBJ or Jam of Various Themes:
Sugar Mag > Hell in a Bucket > Dark Star 13:40-14:40

This is out or print. If they don't want to sell it, the Dead should turn off the block on the Archive.

There really is a quality to this That just doesn't exist with the DP/SBD, which I have owned for years. For instance, the crowd going berserk and fireworks and explosions in the epic Sugar Magnolia > Scarlet Begonias (Bob: "I hope y'all are bein real careful with what you're doin with them bombs") just doesn't translate the same way on the board. Even "To Lay Me Down" is hugely touching on this tape, and since it's a decent recording of the band mixed properly through the sound system, Donna sounds great. Thank you and RIP Jerry Moore for these '74 audience treasures!!!

100% Amazing Wow, this AUD on some good speakers really  puts you in the garden that night!  Check out the fireworks going off in 3D during Sugar Mag.

Then that big jam, I'm sure you've heard the SBD, but listen to this AUD and you can hear the insect fear crawl out of the speakers and get into the crowd - truly frightening!
